Ingenic JZ AES Hardware Accelerator
====================================

Out-of-tree kernel module exposing the AES block found on Ingenic
T-series SoCs as /dev/aes. Userspace programs use an ioctl interface
to run AES-128/192/256 in ECB or CBC mode with DMA.

Supported hardware
------------------
  T10, T20, T21, T23, T30, T31       PRJ007 register layout
  T40, T41                           PRJ007 register layout
  T32, T33                           PRJ008 register layout

The driver auto-selects the layout from CONFIG_SOC_* at build time.
Tested on T31 (1.4 GHz) and T20 (800 MHz).

Supported kernels
-----------------
  3.10, 4.4, 5.15 — DMA alloc and IRQ compat macros cover all three.

Build
-----
Built in-tree by the SDK kernel build (see Kbuild). No standalone
Makefile — sibling misc/ drivers follow the same pattern.

Test programs (test_aes, test_endian, test_le_bit) are userspace
probes/benches. Compile ad hoc with the target toolchain, e.g.:

    mipsel-linux-gcc -O2 -Wall -o test_aes test_aes.c

Install
-------
  insmod jz-aes.ko

Creates /dev/aes (misc device). Any process may open it; the driver
serializes access to the HW engine internally with a mutex.

Files
-----
  jz-aes.c        Kernel module. DMA AES, per-fd session state, HW
                  mutex, key caching, byte-swap flag, combined
                  IOCTL_AES_DO (setkey + encrypt + decrypt in one
                  ioctl for low latency).

  jz-aes.h        Public header. Register definitions for PRJ007 and
                  PRJ008 layouts, ioctl numbers, AES_FLAG_BSWAP.

  test_aes.c      Userspace test + throughput bench. Roundtrips,
                  concurrent-session stress, MB/s measurement.

  test_aes.h      Userspace ioctl/struct definitions (same wire
                  contract as jz-aes.h but without kernel includes).

  test_endian.c   Endianness probe — confirmed key = BE, data = swap
                  on T31.

  test_le_bit.c   ASCR bit-12 (LE mode) probe. Checks whether the
                  SoC has the T32/T33 little-endian data path.

mbedTLS integration
-------------------
The production mbedTLS ALT integration (AES_ALT + CCM_ALT + GCM_ALT
with HW/SW threshold dispatch and per-session scratch buffers)
consuming /dev/aes lives in:

    ~/projects/thingino/jz-crypto/aes/
